<HL>
   Swiss Cost-of-Living Index
</HL>
<DATE>
05/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   BERN -- Switzerland's cost-of-living index rose 0.2% in
April from March, and increased 4.6% from a year earlier, the
government said.
   The April figures represented a slowdown from the March
rises of 0.3% month to month and 5.0% year to year. In the
year-earlier April, the month-to-month increase was 0.5%,
while the year-to-year increase was 2.6%.
</LP>
