<HL>
   Century Telephone Gain
</HL>
<DATE>
05/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   CTL
</CO>
<LP>
   MONROE, La. -- Century Telephone Enterprises Inc. said it
expects to report a $2.2 million second-quarter gain from the
sale of the remainder of its investment in Telecom USA. The
company said the gain is equal to about seven cents a share.
   In the year-ago quarter, Century had net income of $5.3
million, or 18 cents a share, on revenue of $49.2 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The telecommunications concern reported first-quarter net
of $6.8 million, or 22 cents a share, including a $354,000,
or one-cent-a-share, gain from the sale of a portion of its
Telecom stock.
