   The agency said its preliminary figures put world oil
supply in April at 54.2 million barrels a day, down from 54.6
million barrels a day in March, but in line with an average
54.2 million barrels a day for the first quarter. April's
decline was "due almost entirely to a decrease in OPEC
production," the IEA said.
