<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   Levee, Not Levy
</HL>
<DATE>
05/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<LP>
   In the first line of the March 28 Leisure &amp; Arts piece
"Dark Days for Duck," author Michael Pearce says, "I had
stood alone on the levy . . ."
   May I offer the following correction. Levy: the imposition
or collection of an assessment. Levee: an embankment for
preventing flooding.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   When in doubt, remember the lines from that old song,
"Waitin' on the levee, Waitin' for the Robert E. Lee."
   R.R. Regnier
   Phoenix, Ariz.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
