<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Unicorp American Corp., a unit of Unicorp
Canada Corp., said it entered a preliminary agreement with
Coscan Development Corp. regarding the sale of Unicorp
American's real-estate assets.
   Under the agreement, certain Unicorp American real-estate
assets would be transferred to a partnership of Unicorp
American and affiliates of Coscan. Other assets would be
financed with participating mortgages. Net proceeds to
Unicorp American from the transactions, which are expected to
close June 15, would total about $41.6 million and would be
used to repay senior secured debt.
</LP>
<TEXT>
