the assumption of $8 million of mortgages, would be made in
the form of a secured-loan facility to the partnership, and
$17.4 million of participating mortgage would be provided for
other real-estate assets. A Coscan affiliate would be the
managing partner, while Unicorp American would be a limited
partner.
   The agreement requires, among other things, consent of
Unicorp American's lenders. Unicorp Canada plans to
distribute in the third quarter all its common shares of
Unicorp American to holders of Unicorp Canada Class A and B
common.
   Coscan is indirectly controlled by Hees International
Bancorp, a merchant bank controlled by Toronto financiers
Peter and Edward Bronfman. Unicorp Canada is a Toronto
holding company with interest in energy and
financial-services concerns. Hees has a 24.6% non-voting
equity interest in Unicorp Canada.
