</HL>
<DATE>
05/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   HIGH
</CO>
<LP>
   PLYMOUTH, Mich. -- Highland Superstores Inc. reported
April sales of $61.7 million, down 2% from sales of $63.3
million a year ago. Comparable-store sales dropped 6%.
   Highland, a consumer electronics retailer, said its sales
for the first three months of the year were $185.3 million,
down 6% from $196.5 million in the year-earlier period.
Comparable-store sales declined 10%.
</LP>
